Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Once boiled, pour the @water{220%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the @Chicken Stock Paste{1%tbsp} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @Bulgur Wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}.

Pop a lid on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Lamb Mince{200%g} and the pepper. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Use spoon to break the mince up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic and @Harissa Paste{50%g} into the lamb mince. Fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} and remaining @Chicken Stock Paste{1%tbsp}.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the frying pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste the sauce and season with salt, pepper and a pinch more sugar if needed.

Share the bulgur wheat between #bowls{}.

Top with the lamb and sauce.

Spoon over the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g} to finish.

Enjoy!